	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />I apologize if this has been asked already, but is the VRC6 supposed to be so friggin' LOUD on a real Famicom? It almost completely drowns out the 2A03 channels! I have both a modified NES (using the expansion sound mod posted here a while back) and an AV Famicom, and the music in Akumajou Densetsu is much more pleasing on the former, since all the channels are pretty evenly balanced. I also have Gimmick!, which oddly enough, sounds almost the same on both consoles. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_confused.gif" alt=":?" title="Confused" />
<br />
<br />I'm curious as to whether or not the original Famicom had this same "problem"...

		

		</td>
