		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Uh, I think you have that backwards...the cart's output is too loud on the <em>AV Famicom.</em> It sounds perfect on the modded NES.
<br />
<br />Anyway, I just found an <a href="http://nesdev.com/bbs/viewtopic.php?t=245" class="postlink">old topic</a> that suggests I'm not the only one with this problem. At least I know my hardware is working properly.
<br />
<br />I guess it's not a big deal, since I do have the NES + adaptor, but is there a simple mod that would fix the AV Famicom? I like having just one console that plays almost everything in the 8-bit Nintendo universe sitting on my shelf. <img src="./images/smilies/icon_razz.gif" alt=":P" title="Razz" />

		

